<LabLayout title="Lab 28 · Privacy — resolvable private addresses — Firmware Labs" maxWidth={1000}>
  <LabShell
    num="LAB 28"
    title="Privacy — resolvable private addresses"
    tag="GAP privacy"
    why='<b>Where this bites you:</b> "why can&apos;t my device reconnect to the phone after a while?" — because the phone&apos;s address <i>changed</i>. Rotate a few RPAs and resolve them with the bonded IRK to see why bonding matters beyond encryption.'
    takeaway="<b>Why firmware engineers care:</b> if you whitelist/filter by address without storing the <b>IRK</b>, reconnection breaks the moment the phone rotates its RPA — a very common field bug. Controllers resolve RPAs in hardware against the <b>resolving list</b>. RPA = 24-bit prand (top bits 01) + 24-bit hash <code>ah(IRK, prand)</code>; the peer recomputes the hash with each stored IRK and compares."
  >
    <RpaPrivacy />
  </LabShell>
</LabLayout>
